items.title: Stupice tomato as of June 17th
items.description:
livewombat posted a photo:

Stupice is a Czech potato-leaf tomato that is reported to bear early, heavily, and late into the season. Opinions vary widely on whether it tastes good, but this was its first season for us, so this photo was taken before any ripe tomatoes were available to sample.
